I had this same error. version 1.0.1 (or so the package.json says). I was refactoring sweetAlert to an Angular service for reuse.

For me the issue was solved by just wrapping the `swal` call in a function:
function() {
   swal();
}

Something to do with the scope of `this` I think. I guess this is a similar solution as wrapping it in a `setTimeout()` as @BernhardBezdek did. Except that that also puts calling the function at the end of the queue. But - at least in my case - it wasn't an asynchronous issue.

Luckily Ecmascript 6 solved this weird Javascript behaviour with `this`. Now to wait until all browsers support it (or setup that polyfill/transpilation environment).

